Given the following HTML and JavaScript, modify the `clickHandler` in the `App` class using an ES6 arrow function to correctly log the `message` property when the button is clicked. Explain why your solution works.

```html
<button id="myButton">Click Me</button>
```
```javascript
class App {
  constructor(message) {
    this.message = message;
    this.button = document.getElementById('myButton');
    // Problematic line: this.button.addEventListener('click', this.clickHandler);
    // How would you fix this line or the clickHandler?
