questions.example:
```javascript
// Execution Steps:
// 1. console.log('Start') -> 'Start' printed (Synchronous)
// 2. new Promise(resolve => { console.log('Promise constructor'); resolve(); }) -> 'Promise constructor' printed. resolve() schedules the first .then() callback to microtask queue. (Synchronous for constructor)
// 3. setTimeout(() => console.log('Timeout outside Promise'), 0); -> Schedules 'Timeout outside Promise' callback to macrotask queue. (Web API, then Macrotask Queue)
// 4. console.log('End') -> 'End' printed (Synchronous)
// 5. Synchronous code finished. Call stack empty.
// 6. Event Loop checks Microtask Queue. 'Promise then 1' callback is executed. -> 'Promise then 1' printed. Inside this, another setTimeout is scheduled for 'Timeout inside Promise' to the macrotask queue. The second .then() (for 'Promise then 2') is scheduled to the microtask queue.
// 7. Event Loop checks Microtask Queue again. 'Promise then 2' callback is executed. -> 'Promise then 2' printed. (Microtask Queue is now empty).
// 8. Event Loop checks Macrotask Queue. 'Timeout outside Promise' is executed. -> 'Timeout outside Promise' printed.
// 9. Event Loop checks Macrotask Queue again. 'Timeout inside Promise' is executed. -> 'Timeout inside Promise' printed.
```

