questions.answer:
1.  **Logical `&&` Operator**: Used when you want to render something only if a condition is true.
    ```jsx
    {isLoggedIn && <p>Welcome back!</p>}
    ```

2.  **Ternary Operator**: Used when you need to render one of two different things based on a condition (an `if-else` equivalent).
    ```jsx
    {isLoading ? <p>Loading...</p> : <MyDataComponent data={data} />}
    ```

3.  **Immediately Invoked Function Expression (IIFE) or Helper Function**: For more complex conditions or when you want to encapsulate logic.
    ```jsx
    {(() => {
      if (user.role === 'admin') {
        return <AdminPanel />;
      } else if (user.role === 'editor') {
        return <EditorPanel />;
      } else {
        return <GuestView />;
      }
    })()}
    ```
    Or using a helper function:
    ```jsx
    function renderContent() {
      if (user.role === 'admin') return <AdminPanel />;
      if (user.role === 'editor') return <EditorPanel />;
      return <GuestView />;
    }
    return <div>{renderContent()}</div>;
    ```

